    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.001 Selassie I/348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-26T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 26, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 26—11:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>571. Department’s 415, November 23, 2 p.m. I have heard nothing in London about
                    such a visit since my 429, September 11, 2 p.m., and in the circumstances it
                    seemed advisable to confine present inquiries to the Foreign Office which stated
                    that they also have heard nothing.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Repeated to Rome.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
